The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Sunday, October 17, 2004 

 IN THE CITY

 East Bengal defender Debjit Ghosh will join the Bengal squad for the Santosh Trophy on October 24 following an injury to Habibur Rahman Mondal. He is expected to leave for New Delhi on Monday. Meanwhile, Deb Kumar Sashmal and Chinmoy Banerjee on Saturday left for the capital to replace Dipak Mondal and Sandip Nandy in the Bengal squad. Bengal start their campaign on Monday against Mizoram.

 Meanwhile, Anit Ghosh, who played for Mohammedan Sporting this season, turned up at the Mohun Bagan ground on Saturday. However, Bagan assistant secretary Balaram Chowdhury denied that the midfielder is joining their ranks.

 The 28 Bengal Ranji probables will play a four-day practice match as a tune-up to the final selection for the Ranji team. The team will be selected after the Pujas. Meanwhile, the probables, who were training at the Pankaj Gupta Indoor Cricket Coaching Camp, will have a feel of the Jadavpur University ground, in Salt Lake from Monday. 

 CAB will hand over a fitness chart drawn by Bengal?s physical trainer Ranadeep Moitra to the umpires to help them maintain their fitness. Meanwhile, an umpires? seminar was held at Rotary Sadan on Saturday. Former BCCI panel umpires V.K. Ramaswamy and Subrata Banerjee were present in the CAB-organised one-day conclave.

 CRICKET ? Under-17 match? CAB vs Bangladesh XI at Jadavpur University campus, Salt Lake from 10 am.




